##Global Mask emergency, emergency measures taken by many countries, made in China or as a "cure" ?

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

With the spread of new crown pneumonia in the global scope, "mask shortage" phenomenon increased significantly, many countries began to ban the export of masks.

Masks are in short supply in many parts of the world

Face masks are sold in South Korea with odd and even numbers

As the epidemic situation of new crown pneumonia intensifies, the shortage of face masks in the Korean market is becoming more and more serious. Korea will impose restrictions on the purchase of face masks: According to the parity of the year of birth, those born in odd years can only buy face masks on odd days; those born in even years can only buy face masks on even days; and each person can only buy 2 face masks per week.

In addition, the government has decided to increase the proportion of masks sold through public channels such as pharmacies, farmers'associations supermarkets and post offices from the current 50 per cent to more than 80 per cent, and to provide various types of support to mask producers, increase the daily production of face masks from about 10 million to 14 million.

As of March 3, three days after the country's post offices started selling face masks at designated spots, citizens were still suffering from a shortage of supply and queues, the website of Korea's joongang Ilbo reported on March 4. In some areas, people queued up at the post office at 3:50 a.m. and waited more than seven hours to buy five face masks.

Emergency Mask for use in France

The French government has requisitioned all its stocks of face masks because of the rapid spread of the new coronavirus infection, the Reference News reported. President Maqueron announced on twitter: "We are commandeering all respirator stocks and production lines. " He said the masks will be distributed to health care workers and French people infected with the new coronavirus. The government also hopes to prevent panic buying.

Health Minister Ollivier Vaillant said France had so far released 10m masks from its strategic reserve and provided them to hospitals and doctors through pharmacies across the country. France has a total reserve of about 160 million masks. At present, many pharmacies have sold out of masks, some sellers began to sell at a high price.

Japan bans resale of face masks

As of 10:30 local time on June 6,31 new cases had been confirmed in Japan, bringing the total number to 361(including 14 cases of returning planes) , according to NHK.

The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare announced on the evening of the 5th that there were eight more confirmed cases among the passengers of the diamond princess who had previously been quarantined at government facilities. In addition, in order to reduce the previous duplication of statistics, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare adjusted the "Diamond Princess" cruise ship confirmed cases to 696.

In view of the current shortage of face masks in Japan, the government of Japan will prohibit the resale of face masks under the emergency measures for the stability of National Life Act, and offenders will be fined. It is the first time that Japan has banned the resale of face masks by law. In addition, the Japanese government will also purchase 20 million reusable gauze masks, distribution to care institutions and childcare institutions.

Germany to ban exports of face masks and other measures

According to the German "European Times" , the statistics published at 23:30 local time on March 5, Germany, as of March 5,23:30, Germany has a total of 565 confirmed cases of new coronary pneumonia, an increase of nearly 200 cases a day, germany has become the country outside China after South Korea, Italy, Iran, Japan, the fifth-highest number of infected countries. On March 4 local time, the German government introduced a ban on the export of medical protection products, including face masks, called for local segregation of Germans in other EU countries, and strengthened cooperation between the federal and state, among other measures, to strengthen the prevention and control of the epidemic.

What China can do about the global shortage of masks?

Earlier, World Health Organization Director General Tan Desai had said that the global market has been severely disrupted. The demand for masks and other personal protective equipment is already 100 times the normal level and prices 20 times the normal level, and this shortage is further aggravated by the widespread and inappropriate use of personal protective equipment.

Chinese manufacturing is indispensable to solve the global shortage of face masks.

China is a big producer of face masks, accounting for about 50 percent of global annual production, Chinanews.com reported. Before the outbreak, China had a maximum daily production capacity of more than 20 million masks. With the spread of the epidemic, mask demand explosive growth, short-term supply and demand intensified.

To this end, the Chinese government and the business community have made concerted efforts to give priority to ensuring the supply of workers, capital, logistics, and key raw and auxiliary materials for the mask enterprises, and to push the mask enterprises to produce at full steam. The supply of masks has been significantly improved.

According to the dispatch, the daily production capacity of face masks, including face masks, medical masks and N95 face masks, reached 110 million units and 116 million units per day on February 29, the National Development and Reform Commission said on March 2, they are 5.2 times and 12 times of February 1 respectively, further easing the contradiction between supply and demand for face masks.

China's annual exports of face masks have stabilized at more than 70 percent of production, according to official figures. It is worth noting that there have been foreign media reports that China's ban on exports of medical masks and raw materials for production due to the new pneumonia outbreak has caused shortages in other countries and regions.

In response, Li Xinggan, director of the Department of Foreign Trade at the Ministry of Commerce of the People's Republic of China, said on the 5th that China has not put in place any trade control measures for face masks and is willing to provide assistance within the capabilities of the relevant countries in respect of medical protection materials such as face masks.

In response to questions about a series of export restrictions imposed by some countries on products such as face masks and protective clothing, the Ministry of Commerce said recently that in the near future, due to concerns about the spread of the epidemic or the need for national prevention and control, restrictions on the export of face masks, protective clothing, disinfectants and other epidemic prevention and control materials to China by individual countries have had a certain negative impact on us. We understand the practices and reactions of the countries concerned. We also hope that relevant countries will respect the opinions of World Health Organization's experts, continue to give China full understanding and firm support, view the impact of the epidemic objectively and rationally, and refrain from taking excessive trade restrictive measures.

Integrated Chinanews.com, overseas, Reference News, Huanqiu, etc.
